# AIMD Syntax Tour

## Variable Definitions

Enter sample name: {{var|sample_name: str, title = "Sample Name", description = "Human-readable label used throughout this protocol", examples = ["S-001", "Control A"]}}

Operator: {{var|operator: UserName, title = "Operator", description = "Person responsible for running and reviewing this protocol", examples = ["Dr. Chen"]}}

Record time: {{var|current_time: CurrentTime, title = "Record Time", description = "Timestamp captured when the protocol record is prepared", examples = ["2026-05-27 09:30"]}}

Experiment summary: {{var|summary: AiralogyMarkdown, title = "Experiment Summary", description = "Short Markdown note for context, observations, and review comments", examples = ["Initial sample looked clear before mixing."]}}

AIMD content with image refs: {{var|aimd_content: AiralogyMarkdown = "![Site photo](airalogy.id.file.site-photo.png)", title = "AIMD Content With Image Refs", description = "Paste Airalogy Markdown that contains airalogy.id.file.* image references"}}

Extracted image ids: {{var|image_ids: list[str], title = "Extracted Image IDs", description = "Manual client assigner fills this browser-side list from AIMD content"}}

Plasmid sequence: {{var|plasmid_sequence: DNASequence, title = "Plasmid Sequence", description = "Sequence record with topology and feature annotations", examples = ["ATGCGTACGTAGCTAG"]}}

Python analysis snippet: {{var|python_code: PyStr, title = "Python analysis helper"}}

JavaScript formatter: {{var|javascript_code: JsStr, title = "JavaScript formatter"}}

JSON config: {{var|json_config: JsonStr, title = "Structured JSON config"}}

YAML workflow: {{var|yaml_workflow: YamlStr, title = "YAML workflow definition"}}

Generic code block: {{var|generic_code: CodeStr, title = "Language-agnostic code"}}

Temperature setting: {{var|temperature: float = 25.0, title = "Temperature (C)", description = "Ambient temperature used for the run", examples = [25.0, 37.0]}}

Concentration setting: {{var|concentration: float = 1.0, title = "Concentration (M)", description = "Final reagent molarity", examples = [0.5, 1.0, 2.0]}}

Is active: {{var|is_active: bool = true}}

## Review Marks

AIMD supports CriticMarkup-style review marks for editorial review: {++added text++}, {--deleted text--}, {~~old wording~>new wording~~}, {>>review note<<}, and {==highlighted text==}.

## Variable Table

{{var|samples, title = "Sample Measurements", description = "One row per prepared sample", examples = ["S-001 row"], subvars=[
  var(sample_id: str, title = "Sample ID", description = "Tube or plate well identifier", examples = ["S-001"]),
  var(concentration: float, title = "Concentration (M)", description = "Measured reagent molarity", examples = [1.0]),
  var(volume: float, title = "Volume (mL)", description = "Final sample volume", examples = [2.5])
]}}

## Inline Vars In Markdown Table

| Ingredient | Amount |
| --- | --- |
| Water | {{var|water_volume_ml: float}} mL |
| Lemon juice | {{var|lemon_juice_ml: float}} mL |
| Total liquid | {{var|total_liquid_ml: float}} mL |
| Sugar | {{var|sugar_weight_g: float}} g |
| Ice cubes | {{var|ice_cube_count: int}} |

```assigner runtime=client
assigner(
  {
    mode: "auto",
    dependent_fields: ["water_volume_ml", "lemon_juice_ml"],
    assigned_fields: ["total_liquid_ml"],
  },
  function calculate_total_liquid_ml({ water_volume_ml, lemon_juice_ml }) {
    return {
      total_liquid_ml: Math.round((water_volume_ml + lemon_juice_ml) * 100) / 100,
    };
  }
);
```

## Browser-Side List Assigner

This manual client assigner runs entirely in the browser. Click its assigner button next to "Extracted Image IDs" to extract Airalogy file image ids from the AIMD content field above.

```assigner runtime=client
assigner(
  {
    mode: "manual",
    dependent_fields: ["aimd_content"],
    assigned_fields: ["image_ids"],
  },
  function extract_airalogy_image_ids(fields) {
    const text = String(fields.aimd_content || "");
    const image_ids = text.match(/airalogy\.id\.file\.[^\s)]+/g) || [];
    return {
      image_ids: image_ids,
    };
  }
);
```

